\title{Directedness of the interval}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\taxon{Module}
\import{stt-macros}


\subtree[fre-00US]{
\taxon{Idea}
\author{fredrikbakke}

\p{
We consider directedness of the interval, which is the property that every
endofunction on the interval is monotone. In other words, every construction respects
the ordering on #{О”В№}. This condition [generalises](stt-00TV)
[synthetic quasicoherence](Synthetic.Quasicoherence), and is at the same time enough
to derive many important constructions.
}

\p{
Directedness boils down to assuming a canonical equivalence
#{\Hom(\Delta^1,\Delta^1) \simeq (\Delta^1 \to \Delta^1)}, while synthetic
quasicoherence boils down to assuming #{\Delta^2 \simeq (\Delta^1 \to \Delta^1)}.
We demonstrate that, in the absence of assuming any of these conditions, we
have a diagram with retracts:

\quiver{
\begin{tikzcd}
& \Hom(\Delta^1,\Delta^1) \\
\Delta^2 && (\Delta^1 \to \Delta^1)
\arrow[from=1-2, to=2-3, hook]
\arrow[from=2-1, to=1-2, hook]
\arrow[from=1-2, to=2-1, shift left]
\arrow[from=2-1, to=2-3, hook]
\arrow[from=2-3, to=2-1, shift left]
\end{tikzcd}
}
}
}

\agda{
open import Foundations.Universes
open import Algebra.Lattice
open import Algebra.Lattice.Instances.Polynomial
open import Algebra.Order.Monotone

module Synthetic.Directedness {рқ“ҳ} (О”В№ : Type рқ“ҳ) (I : Lattice О”В№) where

open Lattice I renaming (0l to i0; 1l to i1)

open import Axioms.UF
}

\agda-imports{
\agda{
open import Foundations.Prelude
open import Core.Coslices
open import Algebra.Lattice.Instances.Pointwise
open import Modalities.Instances.Truncation

open import Ergonomics.Extensionality
}
}

\subtree[stt-00TV]{
\taxon{Definition}
\title{Directedness of #{О”В№}}
\date{2026-06-11}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\contributor{nimarasekh}
\contributor{reidbarton}

\p{
We say the interval #{О”В№} is \em{directed} if every endofunction on #{О”В№} is
monotone. In other words, every construction respects the ordering on #{О”В№}.
}

\agda{
О”В№-is-directed : Type рқ“ҳ
О”В№-is-directed
  = (f : О”В№ вҶ’ О”В№)
  вҶ’ is-monotone (Lattice.вүӨ-poset I) (Lattice.вүӨ-poset I) f
}
}

\subtree[fre-EB55]{
\taxon{Lemma}
\author{nimarasekh}
\date{2026-06-11}

\agda{
poly-is-mono
  : (s t : О”В№)
  вҶ’ is-monotone (Lattice.вүӨ-poset I) (Lattice.вүӨ-poset I) (О» x вҶ’ (s вҲ§ x) вҲЁ t)
poly-is-mono s t aвүӨb =
  вҲЁ-UP
    ( вҲЁ-вүӨ-introl (вҲ§-UP (вҲ§-вүӨ-eliml вүӨ-refl , вҲ§-вүӨ-elimr aвүӨb))
    , вҲЁ-вүӨ-intror вүӨ-refl)
}
}

\subtree[fre-9F01]{
\title{#{О”ВІ} classifies monomorphisms on #{О”В№}}
\taxon{Definition}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\date{2026-06-30}

\p{
With no extra assumptions, #{О”ВІ} is a retract of monomorphisms on #{О”В№}. In one
direction it is given by evaluation and in the other it is given by forming linear
maps with coefficients in #{О”ВІ}. When this retract is an equivalence we say that
\em{#{О”ВІ} classifies monomorphisms on #{О”В№}}.
}

\agda{
О”ВІвҶҗО”В№-mono
  : PosetHom (Lattice.вүӨ-poset I) (Lattice.вүӨ-poset I) вҶ’ О”ВІ I
О”ВІвҶҗО”В№-mono (f , f-mono) = (f i1 , f i0) вҰғ f-mono 0-init вҰ„

О”ВІ-classifies-О”В№-monos : Type рқ“ҳ
О”ВІ-classifies-О”В№-monos = is-equiv О”ВІвҶҗО”В№-mono

О”В№-monoвҶҗО”ВІ
  : О”ВІ I вҶ’ PosetHom (Lattice.вүӨ-poset I) (Lattice.вүӨ-poset I)
О”В№-monoвҶҗО”ВІ c =
  ((О» i вҶ’ (c .О”ВІ.s вҲ§ i) вҲЁ c .О”ВІ.t) , poly-is-mono (c .О”ВІ.s) (c .О”ВІ.t))

О”ВІвҶҗО”В№-monoвҶҗО”ВІ : О”ВІвҶҗО”В№-mono вҲҳ О”В№-monoвҶҗО”ВІ ~ id
О”ВІвҶҗО”В№-monoвҶҗО”ВІ c =
  О”ВІ-ext
    ( ap (_вҲЁ (c .О”ВІ.t)) 1-top
    вҲҷ вҲЁ-comm
    вҲҷ вүӨ-max (c .О”ВІ.mono)
    , ap (_вҲЁ (c .О”ВІ.t)) (вҲ§-comm вҲҷ 0-init)
    вҲҷ вҲЁ-comm
    вҲҷ 0-bottom)

О”ВІ-retract-of-О”В№-monos
  : retract (О”ВІ I) (PosetHom (Lattice.вүӨ-poset I) (Lattice.вүӨ-poset I))
О”ВІ-retract-of-О”В№-monos = (О”В№-monoвҶҗО”ВІ , О”ВІвҶҗО”В№-mono , О”ВІвҶҗО”В№-monoвҶҗО”ВІ)
}
}

\subtree[stt-00TX]{
\title{#{\Delta^2} is a retract of endomaps on #{\Delta^1}}
\taxon{Lemma}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\date{2026-04-08}

\agda{
О”В№-endoвҶҗО”ВІ : (О”ВІ I) вҶ’ (О”В№ вҶ’ О”В№)
О”В№-endoвҶҗО”ВІ (i , j) x = (i вҲ§ x) вҲЁ j

О”ВІвҶҗО”В№-endo : (О”В№ вҶ’ О”В№) вҶ’ (О”ВІ I)
О”ВІвҶҗО”В№-endo f = (f i0 вҲЁ f i1 , f i0) вҰғ вҲ§-вҲЁ-abs вҰ„

О”ВІ-retract-of-О”В№-endo : retract (О”ВІ I) (О”В№ вҶ’ О”В№)
О”ВІ-retract-of-О”В№-endo
  = ( О”В№-endoвҶҗО”ВІ
    , О”ВІвҶҗО”В№-endo
    , О» ((i , j) вҰғ p вҰ„)
      вҶ’ let f0 = вүӨ-max (вҲ§-вүӨ-elimr 0-init)
            f1 = ap (_вҲЁ j) 1-top вҲҷ вүӨ-max' p
        in О”ВІ-ext (apвӮӮ (_вҲЁ_) f0 f1 вҲҷ вүӨ-max p , f0))
}
}
